# Campus Events Portal – Serverless Web Application on AWS

## Overview

# A fully serverless web application deployed on AWS that allows students to browse campus events, 
register for events, and receive notifications. The system is designed using cloud-native 
architecture to ensure scalability, security, and high availability.

# Key Features

Browse and explore campus events through a web interface

Online event registration system for students

Automated event notification system

Secure authentication and access control

Scalable serverless architecture using AWS services

# Technical Highlights 

## Cloud Architecture

Designed and deployed a fully serverless web application architecture on AWS

Implemented event-driven backend using AWS Lambda

Built REST APIs using Amazon API Gateway

## Data Management

Stored and managed event data using Amazon DynamoDB

Implemented efficient CRUD operations for event registration

## Frontend Hosting

Hosted static frontend website on Amazon S3

Distributed globally using Amazon CloudFront CDN for improved performance

## Security

Implemented secure authentication using Amazon Cognito

Managed permissions and roles using AWS IAM

## Notifications

Integrated Amazon SNS to send event registration notifications to users

## Domain and Networking

Configured custom domain using Amazon Route 53


# Architecture Components

The system uses the following AWS services:

Amazon S3 – Static website hosting

Amazon CloudFront – Content delivery network

Amazon API Gateway – REST API layer

AWS Lambda – Serverless backend logic

Amazon DynamoDB – NoSQL database

Amazon Cognito – User authentication

Amazon SNS – Notification service

AWS IAM – Security and access control

Amazon Route 53 – Domain management

